ssh-keygen -t rsa
# generante a cryptographic key pair
# -t  = specifies the type of key to create (“rsa” for protocol version 2)
# the command will start up an interactive series of prompts asking you:
#  - a filename where you want to store the key (default = id_rsa)
#  - a pass phrase to unlock the key (not to log into the remote server itself)